    <div class="substitution">

      <h4 class="name">Substitution Cipher</h4>

      <h5 class="description">Description</h5>

      <div class="row">
        <p class="descBody col s8 offset-s2">
          A simple substitution cipher is a cipher where we choose a random number for each character and only use it once for that
          specific character. This means that there is billions of options that we cannot be figured out.
          To encrypt it we use the bottom row and to decrypt it we use the top row.
          The simple substitution can not be hack by a brute-force attack.
        </p>
        <p class="descBody col s8 offset-s2">
          The simple substitution is more complex that the other ciphers. We need to employ a clever way to do this.
          We have to check a word pattern for each word, and each word and the plaintext will always the same word pattern.
          SO we compute all the possible candidates and then create a mapping for all the possible encryption letters.
          The longer the message the more easier is is to hack it.
        </p>
      </div>

